# Sprint 227 TDD red-state log

Date: 2026-05-06.

## Process

Generator captured the red→green TDD trajectory by writing the
backend Rust fixtures + frontend vitest cases first, then making the
implementation changes pass. The intermediate "red" output below
records the canonical failure modes that drove each implementation
decision.

## Phase 1 — Rust unit fixtures (RED)

Goal: prove the COMMENT ON COLUMN emission contract before extending
`create_table` to emit the new statements.

After authoring the new fixtures (without modifying mutations.rs):

    cargo test --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml create_table

    test result: FAILED. 5 newly-added cases in
    `db::postgres::mutations::tests::create_table_*` failed because
    the SQL builder still produced the Sprint 226 single-statement
    `CREATE TABLE` text without any `COMMENT ON COLUMN` suffix:

      create_table_preview_two_columns_one_comment_byte_equivalent
      create_table_preview_single_quote_escape_byte_equivalent
      create_table_preview_whitespace_comment_emits_no_statement
      create_table_preview_comment_with_semicolon_does_not_split
      create_table_preview_zero_comment_byte_equivalent_to_sprint_226

    The Sprint 226 fixture
    `create_table_preview_three_column_composite_pk_byte_equivalent`
    continued to PASS (regression-locked).

After extending `create_table` to walk the column list and append
`COMMENT ON COLUMN "<schema>"."<table>"."<col>" IS '<escaped>';` per
non-empty comment, all 16 `create_table_*` cases passed (Sprint 226's
11 + Sprint 227's 5).

## Phase 2 — vitest CreateTableDialog suite (RED)

Goal: prove the AC-227-01..08 surface (tabs / schema dropdown /
combobox / comment input / inline preview pane / Keys tab PK / footer
parity / Sprint 226 carry-over).

Initial run after writing AC-227 cases against the Sprint 226 modal
body (no changes):

    pnpm vitest run src/components/schema/CreateTableDialog.test.tsx

    Tests  ~10 failed (~13 passed). Failures included:
      - `getAllByRole("tab")` length expected 4, got 0 (modal had no
        Tabs primitive yet).
      - `screen.getByRole("combobox", { name: "Target schema" })`
        threw `Unable to find element` (no schema dropdown header).
      - `within(columnsPanel).getByRole("combobox", { name: "Column
        data type" })` threw (the type input was a plain `<input>`).
      - `Column comment` aria-label not found.
      - `Show DDL` button not found (footer still had `Preview SQL`).
      - `previewPane.textContent` did not contain `COMMENT ON`
        (modal-on-modal `SqlPreviewDialog` rendered text instead).
      - Sprint 226 IPC sequence test failed because the new flow runs
        through `Show DDL` → `Execute` (not `Preview SQL` → `Execute`).

After redesigning `CreateTableDialog.tsx` (Tabs + Target schema
dropdown + `CreateTableTypeCombobox` + comment input + inline
collapsible preview pane + footer Cancel/Execute) and migrating
Sprint 226 cases to tab-aware queries, all 23 cases passed.

