## Phase 4 — SchemaTree.actions entry-point regression

Goal: keep AC-226-05 entry-point tests passing under the new tab-aware
modal surface (mechanical query-selector adaptation only — no
assertion text-string changes).

Initial run after Phase 2 changes:

    pnpm vitest run src/components/schema/SchemaTree.actions.test.tsx

    Tests  3 failed | 33 passed (36).

    Failures: AC-226-05 entry-point cases asserted the (now removed)
    `getByLabelText("Schema name")` and `getByRole("button", {
    name: /Preview SQL/i })`. The Sprint 227 modal no longer renders
    those — it surfaces a `Target schema` Select trigger and a
    `Show DDL` toggle button.

Mechanical migration:
  - `getByLabelText("Schema name")` →
    `getByRole("combobox", { name: "Target schema" })` + textContent
    contains assertion.
  - `getByRole("button", { name: /Preview SQL/i })` →
    `getByRole("button", { name: "Show DDL" })`.
  - All other assertion text strings (`Create Table` heading,
    Sprint 226 IPC sequence, `loadTables` post-commit refresh count)
    preserved verbatim.

After mechanical migration:

    Tests  36 passed (36).

